features: ✨ SPIRAL JOURNAL - This package includes 3 pack college ruled spiral notebooks, which with classic ruled pages design for everyday use + water-resistant design + 160 Pages (80 Sheets) per journal + 7mm Lines width + Inner Pocket + Elastic Closure Band + Perfect A5 size(5.7" x 8.4") to carry in a backpack for easy everyday outing.

✨ PREMIUM THICK PAPER - 160 ruled pages made from premium thicker paper than normal paper in the market reduce ink leakage, erase fraying and shade issues + White and acid-free paper + Sturdy twin-wire binding keeps your notebook intact.

✨ LAY-FLAT 180° RULED NOTEBOOK - Brightly colored flower patterns are used as the main design. The positive words part is made of hot stamping, which is exquisite and waterproof. Lay and open flat with 180°lay-flat design for reading and writing more easy and efficient. This journal notebook can be folded 360°freely without folding creases,also facilitate you to tear pages and prevent paper fall apart.

✨ BACK POCKET & BANDED - Sturdy expandable back pocket in case you need to tuck any loose items in back + Elastic closure band to keep your ruled notebook closed when not in use or when transported in your backpack.

✨ EVERYDAY USE & GIFT CHOICE - Write down your story, note-taking in classes or meetings, sketching, writing thoughts and ideas, keeping memories with this ruled notebook + Your friends and family will love this pretty journal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice set of journals
reviews.reviewText: I do a lot of journaling and these are my favorite. Love the spiral binding that allows them to lie flat, making it easy to journal. The paper is thick enough that it doesn't bleed thru when writing on both sides of the sheet. (I use a thin line Pentel ink pen) Colors are beautiful and cheerful and I love the little pocket and elastic on the back cover. Will definitely purchase again.

reviews.reviewText: I bought a package of three, and I am pleased with the quality of the journal. It seems the price and the quality are fair. I don’t Think that I would give it as a gift because it seems like a more day today shoving your purse, shove in your briefcase item, versus a gift. Not sure about the durability either, cause I haven’t had it that long, but the Amazon app won’t let me change my five star to a four star
